<br>
I'm Wiccan, so I don't have much time for sin and hell and all that rot.  But assuming Eden for the sake of argument, as the perfectly valid metaphor it is (wish all the thumpers would realize that this is all metaphor) then I see Eden as the nursery of Mankind, and the apple as the final exam.  At some point the child has to separate from the parents and become self-realized.  Jehovah put that apple in the Garden for the day those two were ready to stop loafing about and start things.  He was about to kick Adam's butt for stalling when finally Eve took the initiative.  Yay Eve!<br>
<br>
So in best booming voice, Jehovah said &quot;Get the heck out then, find someplace else to call home&quot; and try as he might, he couldn't quite hide the outrageous smirk on his face.<br>
<br>
Seriously, I have no problem with anyone's religion or lack thereof.  Sometimes people get in my face and tell me I'm Wrong and they are Right  and I say yeah, whatever.<br>
